Description: sabinaNSDM is an R package designed for the development of spatially-nested species distribution models (NSDMs), integrating global and regional scale data. It automates key steps such as data preparation, model calibration, and projection, providing a unified framework for ecologists and conservationists to make reliable predictions about species distributions across scales.
